<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8324> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8324" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These men were witnesses to the resolutions of the Senate reported by Caelius to Cicero in Fam. 8.8.5-6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7466> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7466" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Shackleton Bailey (CLA, 4.342, on Att. 8.11A) notes that he is not listed among the five senators that Caesar captured at Corfinium (BC 1.23.2), and so had probably succeeded in escaping before the town was taken. The full name as above is given in Cic. Fam. 8.8.5.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5678> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5678" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pompey's Envoy to the Parthian court (Caes. BC 3.82.5; see 49, Envoys)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5591> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5591" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Legate under Pompey, who retreated before Caesar's advance from Camerium. to Corfinium where he was captured (Caes. BC 1.15.5; cf. Cic. Att. 8.11A), but upon release went off to join Pompey (Caes. BC 1.23.2). See above, Legates, Envoys." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5570> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5570" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Pompey to ask aid from the Parthians (Caes. BC 3.82.4; cf. Dio 42.2.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5276> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5276" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, on Coelius Vinicianus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5274> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5274" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.781. Together with Hirrus he proposed that Pompey be made Dictator, but failed to carry it (Cael., in Cic. Fam. 8.4.3; Plut. Pomp. 54.2-3; cf. Cic. QF 3.4.1, and 8.4, and 9.3; Dio 40.45, cf. 17.1; Obseq. 63)." .
